<br>
The creature AI is wild. Some creatures will come up to you and mew at you if you are too close to their herd, other creatures will come running up to you, yap at you and then run away. Most sentient beings are line of sight agro, if you are KOS to them. You spawn your own missions, pick the creature you want to tangle with and get credits for it.<br>
<br>
Rebel/Imperial fighting goes down in cities, player and npc like. Some parts of the cities are dangerous for lower level folks, muggers and such prowl the streets.<br>
<br>
Almost no zoning.<br>
<br>
As for creating a character? Amazing. My character is a zabrak, darth maul race, he is on his way to becoming a cloner and a creature handler. He will be able to spice DNA to create beasts that he can bring out on the battle field.<br>
<br>
Downsides. The servers are still buggy, strange things happen sometimes. You need a monster system to run the game effectively. Best to have a gig ram for no lag.<br>
<br>
